  <description type="morphology">Leaves pubescent, villous, or sericeous (distal with hairs not notably longer at margins), all or distal glandular. Heads in paniculiform arrays. Peduncles 0 or 1–30 mm, bracts not surpassing phyllaries. Calyculi 0. Phyllaries 3.5–6.5 mm, apices usually shorter than bodies. Ray florets 5–11; laminae white, abaxially purple-veined. Cypsela widths 0.5–0.6 times lengths. 2n = 28.</description>
